  <p id="JHJZMo">Apple has just released <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24170653/apple-watch-watchos-11-features-updates-wwdc">watchOS 11</a>, the latest version of its smartwatch operating system, alongside <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24172132/apple-ios-18-new-features-ai">iOS 18</a> and <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/16/24194423/math-notes-ipad-ios-18-calculator-app">iPadOS 18</a>. The update, <a href="https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/09/watchos-11-is-available-today/">available for the Apple Watch Series 6</a> and later models, will finally allow users to take rest days without breaking their activity streak and introduces <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/16/24246150/apple-watch-sleep-apnea-detection-fda-approval">FDA-cleared</a> <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/9/24240045/apple-watch-sleep-apnea-detection-feature-series-9-10-ultra-2">sleep apnea detection</a>.</p>
